\fs52 Saving a Terminal Configuration for Later Use\

\fs16 \
\
\pard\tx2480\tx2860\tx3240\li2100\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs28 \cf0 Information about a window or set of windows can be saved to a file, allowing you to save your preferred configurations for later use.  Everything about each window is saved except the contents of the scrollback buffer\'d0this includes the shell, the size and location of the window on the screen, the title bar and font characteristics, and whether or not the window is miniaturized.  To save a configuration, choose Save (or Save As) in the Shell menu.  Terminal appends a 
\f4\b .term
\f0\b0  file extension to the file name you specify.  Since Terminal looks for configuration files in your 
\f4\b ~/Library/Terminal
\f0\b0  directory, this is where you should save them.\
\pard\tx2480\tx2860\tx3240\li2100\partightenfactor0

\fs16 \cf0 \
\pard\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\

\fs28 \
