\fs16 \
\
\pard\tx2480\tx2860\tx3240\li2100\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs28 \cf0 Although by default Terminal doesn\'92t make services available to other applications via the Services menu, Terminal does contain a Terminal Services panel that you can use to define any services you want Terminal to provide.\
\pard\tx2480\tx2860\tx3240\li2100\partightenfactor0

\fs16 \cf0 \
\pard\tx2480\tx2860\tx3240\li2100\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 To open the Terminal Services panel, choose Terminal Services in the Info menu.  If no Terminal services are defined, you\'92ll see a panel asking if you want to load a set of example services.  You may find it useful to load and examine this set of examples, and then remove any you don\'92t want to keep.\
\pard\tx2480\tx2860\tx3240\li2100\partightenfactor0

